parameters: \n<Rui>Haa... haa... If I've made it this far...!

\n<Rui>...(There's no sign of anything... I've completely shaken
them off! Now, to deal with the coagulation crystal...)

\n<Rui>The barrier is completely gone!! I have no choice but to
throw it into the sea... No, there are monsters in the sea
too! I have to throw it as far away as possible, or it'll be
found immediately...

\n<Rui>Ugh... uweeeeh!!! No, I can't! I can't touch this anymore...
I feel nauseous...!!
\n<???>(You've done well, Rui.)
\n<Rui>Wh... who...? Whose voice...
\n<Cat Borrower>(It's me.)
\n<Rui>Eh...? Cat Borrower? The hand... spoke...?

\n<Cat Borrower>(I will take the coagulation crystal and sink it to the
bottom of the distant sea, in a deep sea where no monsters
dwell. So, don't worry anymore.)

\n<Cat Borrower>(Magical power dissolves in water. Even a mass of malice
like this will eventually become part of the vast ocean and
naturally fade away over time.)

\n<Cat Borrower>(Ugh... this is quite a nasty piece of work. It feels
disgusting...)

\n<Cat Borrower>(The reason Chelsea couldn't use the Cat Borrower was that I
thought she didn't need it. She's straightforward and
strong, never wavering.)

\n<Cat Borrower>(However, you twins are different. Special twins. Innate
talent. Born status. You've been pampered and grown arrogant
due to your superiority over others, and there's a danger of
straying from the path.)

\n<Cat Borrower>(Rui... no, Wanzworth. You were a very troublesome
daughter.)
\n<Cat Borrower>(Rui... no, Luisham. You were a very troublesome son.)
\n<Rui>Mo... mother...?

\n<Cat Borrower>(But now you're fine. You've gone outside, interacted with
people, clashed with them, been led astray, but you've come
this far without making mistakes.)

\n<Cat Borrower>(There's nothing to worry about. Both Luisham and Wanzworth
are my pride and joy.)

\n<Cat Borrower>(Seize your future with your own hands. This is the last
time I lend you a hand.)
\n<Cat Borrower>(But I'm always watching over you. My dear children.)
\n<Rui>Ah... don't go...
\n<Rui>...

\n<Rui>Thank you for everything!! I can do it too! Because I'm your
child, mom! I can do it! I will do it!!

\n<Rui>Thank you for everything!! I'll try even harder!! Because
I'm a proud member of the Catfield family!

Afterwards, the horde of monsters including Terra lost sight
of the coagulation crystal and were mostly repelled by the
efforts of the Lumare Guard, with the survivors giving up
and leaving.

The damage to Dreen was severe, but reconstruction is
progressing smoothly with cooperation from Lumare.

Count Noblesse was imprisoned after his conspiracy was
exposed. The fact that he tried to bury the slum dwellers
alive was made public. However, there are still not a few
among the residents of the noble district who support him.

Custom is a frightening thing; despite everything that
happened, slum dwellers still drink during the day and
residents of the noble district continue to litter.

Just because they fought together once doesn't mean that
years of resentment were instantly resolved.

But things are steadily changing. Everyone, both high and
low, can feel it. Even if it's just a little, they're trying
to truly understand each other.
And as for us...
And as for us boys...
